info.description:
OpenAPI 3.0 based swagger docs for Element Public API.

If you have questions, Please review HelpCenter for help, Or Contact Us.

post.description:
This endpoint is used to create listing or offers on the Element contract.It is recommended to use the Element SDK to signature order parameters and place order.
Make Listings
Make Offers

side.description: Side of the order. 0 for buy orders and 1 for sell orders.

saleKind.description: Kind of sell order. 0 for standard order, 3 for bulk listings.

paymentToken.description: The address of the smart contract of the payment token that is accepted or offered by the order. Native token is 0x0000000000000000000000000000000000000000.

basePrice.description:
The base price is the total price of the order, minus the fees.
For example:
totalPrice = unitPrice * quantity.
fees = totalPrice * (feeBps / 10000).
basePrice = totalPrice - fees.

extra.description: The lowest selling price for Dutch auctions or the reserve price for British auctions, differentiated by saleKine (price increase/decrease percentage), default is 0.

listingTime.description: Listing Time, default value is the current time minus 60 seconds.

expirationTime.description: Expiration Time, must be less than the current time plus 7,890,048  seconds  (3 months).

properties.description: Optional. Only the combined offer can be used

items.description: Optional. Only the combined offer can be used

signatureType.description:
Signature Type.
0 = EIP712 
1 = PRESIGNED 
2 = EIP712_BULK 
3 = EIP712_1271 
4 = EIP712_BULK_1271

side.description: Side of the order. 0 for buy orders and 1 for sell orders.

paymentToken.description: The address of the smart contract of the payment token that is accepted or offered by the order

items.description: Optional. Only the combined offer can be used

post.description:
Element is an aggregation platform. In order to be compatible with various platform protocols, Element API uses 0x000000000000000000000000000000000000000 to represent the Native Token. However, in the operation of contract interaction and signature, it is necessary to follow the original Native Token definition of each platform. Where Element is 0xEeeeeEeeeEeEeeEeEeEeeEEEeeeeEeeeeeeeeEEeE, OpenSea„ÄÅLooksRare is 0x000000000000000000000000000000000000000. 

You must use the 'v1/orders/fetchExchangeData' API to fetch exchangeData of this order, then use 'exchangeData.erc20Token' to interact with contracts.

paymentToken.description: Payment token

price.description: Order price, the unit is ether

side.description: Side of the order. 0 for buy orders and 1 for sell orders.

saleKind.description: 0 for standard order, 3 for bulk listings, 7 for collection offer.

paymentToken.description: Payment Token.

side.description: Order side.

saleKind.description: Order sale kind, 0 for standard order, 3 for bulk listings, 7 for collection offer.

price.description: Order price, the unit is ether

isValid.description: Is valid.First judge this field. If it is true, it means that the order was found. If it is false, it means that the order was not found. For details, please refer to errorDetail

priceBase.description: The price in the base currency of the current chain (Ethereum is converted to eth, bsc is bnb).

get.description:
This endpoint can be used to fetch the latest order nonce value.
The nonce for each order is unique and incremented each time..

parameters.name: count
parameters.description: The number of nonces occupied this time, The default is 1, for example: count is 5, and the returned data is 100, then the valid nonce range returned is [100, 100+5-1].

get.description: This endpoint can be used to fetch orders from the system

parameters.name: asset_contract_address
parameters.description: Filter by smart contract address for the asset category.When this field is empty, only the parameters chain, side, direction, listed_after, limit, offset will affect the query result, other parameters will be ignored.

parameters.name: token_ids
parameters.description: Filter by a list of token IDs for the order's asset, comma separated. Needs to be defined together with asset_contract_address.

parameters.name: sale_kind
parameters.description: Filter by the kind of sell order, 0 for standard order, 3 for bulk listings, 7 for collection offer, default for all orders.

parameters.name: side
parameters.description: Filter by the side of the order. 0 for buy orders and 1 for sell orders.

parameters.name: maker
parameters.description: Filter by the order maker's wallet address

parameters.name: taker
parameters.description: Filter by the order taker's wallet address. Orders open for any taker have the null address as their taker.

parameters.name: payment_token
parameters.description: Filter by the address of the smart contract of the payment token that is accepted or offered by the order, Native token is 0x0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 for sell order. Leave blank to query all paymentToken orders.

parameters.name: order_by
parameters.description: How to sort the orders. Can be created_date for when they were made, or base_price to see the lowest-priced orders first, when using created_date, the results are sorted by listingTime. use with direction, created_date is default.

parameters.name: direction
parameters.description: Can be asc or desc for ascending or descending sort. use with order_by, desc is default.

parameters.name: listed_before
parameters.description: Only show orders listed before this timestamp(order createdTime). Seconds since the Unix epoch.

parameters.name: listed_after
parameters.description: Only show orders listed after this timestamp(order createdTime). Seconds since the Unix epoch.

parameters.name: limit
parameters.description: Number of orders to return (capped at 50, default is 20).

parameters.name: offset
parameters.description: Number of orders to offset by (for pagination), When asset_contract_address is not provided, max offset is 10000.

side.description: Side of the order. 0 for buy orders and 1 for sell orders.

saleKind.description: Kind of sell order. 0 for standard order, 3 for bulk listings, 7 for collection offer.

paymentToken.description: The address of the smart contract of the payment token that is accepted or offered by the order

priceBase.description: The price in the base currency of the current chain (Ethereum is converted to eth, bsc is bnb), the unit is ether.

price.description: The order price in paymentToken, the unit is ether.

get.description: This endpoint can be used to Query Aggregate Orders from multiple markets (Element,OpenSea,LooksRare).You must use the 'v1/orders/fetchExchangeData' API to fetch exchangeData of this order, then use 'exchangeData.erc20Token' to interact with contracts.

parameters.name: chain
parameters.description: Chain name, which the asset belongs, Supported chains: eth, polygon, bsc, avalanche, arbitrum, zksync, linea, starknet, opbnb, base, scroll, manta_pacific, optimism, mantle, zkfair, eth is default

parameters.name: markets
parameters.description: Filter by the market, support markets: element, opensea, looksrare. empty for all market.

parameters.name: tokens
parameters.description: Filter by the asset token ids, comma separated.

parameters.name: sort_type
parameters.description: Sort type for the result. bestLowToHigh is default.

parameters.name: direction
parameters.description: Support -asc (positive order) desc (reverse order) default desc.

parameters.name: page_size
parameters.description: Result page size, max 50, 20 for default.

bestAskValid.description: When the field is true, bestAskOrder has data, and when it is false, there is no data

get.description:
This endpoint can be used to fetch asset event list from the system, query by collection slug or combined query by chain, contractAddress and tokenId. The Sale events include all markets. The Listing/Cancel events include Element,OpenSea,LooksRare,X2Y2...

Asset Events: Only fill in 'collection_slugs' or 'contract_address' and 'token_id' will get events of this asset.

Collection Events: Only fill in 'collection_slugs' or 'contract_address' will get all events of these collections.

Market Events: If neither 'collection_slugs' nor 'contract_address' nor 'token_id' are filled in, you must fill in markets, events of all collections in markets will be obtained.

parameters.name: markets
parameters.description: Markets, allow values: Element, OpenSea, X2Y2, LooksRare, tofuNFT, case sensitive and comma separated.

parameters.name: event_names
parameters.description: Filter by event names, allow values: Sale,Minted,List,Offer,Transfer,CollectionOffer,BidCancel,Cancel, comma separated. If filtered by market, Minted, Transfer are not support.

cursor.description: The cursor of this event in system.

paymentToken.description: Asset event payment token

price.description: Asset event price

orignEventAddress.description: The contract address of the actual transaction
